Text.SourceString: I’m only allowed to go to the Winter Fair with my parents. They said they didn’t want me getting lost in the crowd.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m only allowed to go to the Winter Fair with my parents. They said they didn’t want me getting lost in the crowd.

Text.SourceString: We’re learning how to sing and play instruments at school!//<portrait=normal>Wanna hear me sing?
Text.LocalizedString: We’re learning how to sing and play instruments at school!//<portrait=normal>Wanna hear me sing?

Text.SourceString: Oh, I know! I’m going to sing at one of the festivals!//That way, everybody can hear me sing.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I know! I’m going to sing at one of the festivals!//That way, everybody can hear me sing.

Text.SourceString: It was so much fun playing at the vineyard last weekend. <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> made lots of pasta… Mmm! Yummy! I got to take some home for dinner too.
Text.LocalizedString: It was so much fun playing at the vineyard last weekend. <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> made lots of pasta… Mmm! Yummy! I got to take some home for dinner too.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to keep my rock collection small.//<portrait=annoyed>Mom said I can’t keep bringing so many rocks home, so I have to pick more carefully.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to keep my rock collection small.//<portrait=annoyed>Mom said I can’t keep bringing so many rocks home, so I have to pick more carefully.

Text.SourceString: But it’s <Italic>sooooo</> hard! There are so many cool, shiny rocks.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s <Italic>sooooo</> hard! There are so many cool, shiny rocks.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> comes over to the house and talks to Mom for a long time.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> comes over to the house and talks to Mom for a long time.

Text.SourceString: I’d rather play with <NPCName>Taco</> or the ducks at the ranch. They’re way more fun than listening to grown-up talk.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d rather play with <NPCName>Taco</> or the ducks at the ranch. They’re way more fun than listening to grown-up talk.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> makes us read a lot of books, and we talk about them after. It’s so much fun!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> makes us read a lot of books, and we talk about them after. It’s so much fun!

Text.SourceString: Well, some of them are cool. We get to read about the planets and stuff… But some of them are super boring.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, some of them are cool. We get to read about the planets and stuff… But some of them are super boring.

Text.SourceString: I like going to the library.
Text.LocalizedString: I like going to the library.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Millie</> lets us look at the new books sometimes.//<portrait=normal>I like her. She’s supercool.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Millie</> lets us look at the new books sometimes.//<portrait=normal>I like her. She’s supercool.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Luke</> lets me play with his dog, <NPCName>Taco</>, as long as I’m careful with him.//<portrait=doubt>He said <NPCName>Taco</> can’t eat everything I eat, so I gotta be careful giving him treats. So he doesn’t get a tummy ache.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Luke</> lets me play with his dog, <NPCName>Taco</>, as long as I’m careful with him.//<portrait=doubt>He said <NPCName>Taco</> can’t eat everything I eat, so I gotta be careful giving him treats. So he doesn’t get a tummy ache.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> can’t eat grapes…chocolate…errr…what else?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> can’t eat grapes…chocolate…errr…what else?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> told me that to be a vet, I need to do lots of reading.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> told me that to be a vet, I need to do lots of reading.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind it. I like reading… And my mom, and burritos, <Italic>and</> ice cream!//<portrait=normal>I like a lot of things.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind it. I like reading… And my mom, and burritos, <Italic>and</> ice cream!//<portrait=normal>I like a lot of things.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is Friday, then the weekend! Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is Friday, then the weekend! Yay!

Text.SourceString: I wonder what we’re gonna do tomorrow at school.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what we’re gonna do tomorrow at school.

Text.SourceString: Happy Monday! What do farmers do on Mondays?
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Monday! What do farmers do on Mondays?

Text.SourceString: I wish I could go to the forest today and look for bugs. But Dad is busy, so I think we’re gonna go tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could go to the forest today and look for bugs. But Dad is busy, so I think we’re gonna go tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: We learned fancy words at school like “photosynthesis” and “symbiosis.” We’re studying science about plants.//My uncle knows a lot about it.
Text.LocalizedString: We learned fancy words at school like “photosynthesis” and “symbiosis.” We’re studying science about plants.//My uncle knows a lot about it.

Text.SourceString: Symbiosis is when two things work close together for a long time. I think…//<portrait=doubt>Is that right? Do you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Symbiosis is when two things work close together for a long time. I think…//<portrait=doubt>Is that right? Do you know?

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad are carpenters. They get to make things all day from wood and stones.//They help people build their houses – walls, roofs, and everything.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad are carpenters. They get to make things all day from wood and stones.//They help people build their houses – walls, roofs, and everything.

Text.SourceString: They make houses for animals too… Huge, giant barns and coops!
Text.LocalizedString: They make houses for animals too… Huge, giant barns and coops!

Text.SourceString: Mom sends Dad and me to find bananas in the forest when she wants to make banana fritters.//<portrait=happy>It’s my dad’s favorite!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom sends Dad and me to find bananas in the forest when she wants to make banana fritters.//<portrait=happy>It’s my dad’s favorite!

Text.SourceString: Mom said bananas from <NPCName>Sam’s</> store aren’t as good as the ones we find.//Dad said they’re too expensive, so they don’t taste as good.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom said bananas from <NPCName>Sam’s</> store aren’t as good as the ones we find.//Dad said they’re too expensive, so they don’t taste as good.

Text.SourceString: I don’t take bugs home.//I usually just play with them and put them back on the grass. Mom said I shouldn’t take anything home from the forest unless we can eat it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t take bugs home.//I usually just play with them and put them back on the grass. Mom said I shouldn’t take anything home from the forest unless we can eat it.

Text.SourceString: I’m hungry… I want some snacks.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m hungry… I want some snacks.

Text.SourceString: Do you just walk around the island on the weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you just walk around the island on the weekend?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> said that <NPCName>Macy</> has a cool new video game, and she’s gonna let us play it.//I hope Mom lets me go to the inn to try it out.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> said that <NPCName>Macy</> has a cool new video game, and she’s gonna let us play it.//I hope Mom lets me go to the inn to try it out.

Text.SourceString: She always says the inn is too far away… But I don’t think it’s far away!
Text.LocalizedString: She always says the inn is too far away… But I don’t think it’s far away!

Text.SourceString: I added all the birds and bugs I saw over the weekend to my journal. I can’t wait for everybody to see it at show-and-tell tomorrow!
Text.LocalizedString: I added all the birds and bugs I saw over the weekend to my journal. I can’t wait for everybody to see it at show-and-tell tomorrow!

Text.SourceString: Do you like our classroom decorations?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like our classroom decorations?

Text.SourceString: I left my reading notes at home again… Now I won’t be able to talk about it that much.
Text.LocalizedString: I left my reading notes at home again… Now I won’t be able to talk about it that much.

Text.SourceString: Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: Umm…

Text.SourceString: Do you want my lunch? I think I’ll get tacos today.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you want my lunch? I think I’ll get tacos today.

Text.SourceString: When I grow up, I want to visit forests all over the world and see what kind of animals live there!
Text.LocalizedString: When I grow up, I want to visit forests all over the world and see what kind of animals live there!

Text.SourceString: Mom said I can…
Text.LocalizedString: Mom said I can…

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna go in and get some juice… <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> said I could take whatever I want from her fridge.//She’s so nice.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna go in and get some juice… <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> said I could take whatever I want from her fridge.//She’s so nice.

Text.SourceString: I ate all my burrito… Now what?
Text.LocalizedString: I ate all my burrito… Now what?

Text.SourceString: Whoa, look at these comic books!
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, look at these comic books!

Text.SourceString: Oh man! I forgot to wash the rocks I got last week.//Mom is gonna be mad when she goes in my room.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh man! I forgot to wash the rocks I got last week.//Mom is gonna be mad when she goes in my room.

Text.SourceString: Oh well… Too late. Can’t do anything now.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well… Too late. Can’t do anything now.

Text.SourceString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.

Text.SourceString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.

Text.SourceString: This one is new. The kite… I was talking about my new kite.
Text.LocalizedString: This one is new. The kite… I was talking about my new kite.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, it looks the same. Ha ha ha! It’s the only shape I know how to make!
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, it looks the same. Ha ha ha! It’s the only shape I know how to make!

Text.SourceString: Aww, no… I wish I’d brought my box of rocks. I think they’d look nice and shiny here.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww, no… I wish I’d brought my box of rocks. I think they’d look nice and shiny here.

Text.SourceString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.

Text.SourceString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.

Text.SourceString: Being outside is so much fun.//<portrait=happy>Also, you can smell <NpcName>Emma’s</> tacos from here. So yummy.
Text.LocalizedString: Being outside is so much fun.//<portrait=happy>Also, you can smell <NpcName>Emma’s</> tacos from here. So yummy.

Text.SourceString: What do you think I should do next?//Hmm… Maybe I should play basketball.
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think I should do next?//Hmm… Maybe I should play basketball.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> likes to teach outside sometimes.//But never on rainy days. We’re always inside when it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName> Mr. Barnes</> likes to teach outside sometimes.//But never on rainy days. We’re always inside when it rains.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t bring my jump rope today. Maybe I can borrow <NpcName>Valentina’s</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t bring my jump rope today. Maybe I can borrow <NpcName>Valentina’s</>.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and sunny today, so our class is out here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and sunny today, so our class is out here.

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad do yoga here on the weekend.//I don’t wanna join in, because I don’t like yoga.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad do yoga here on the weekend.//I don’t wanna join in, because I don’t like yoga.

Text.SourceString: That building over there, the community center, is massive inside!//It must have taken a long time to build.
Text.LocalizedString: That building over there, the community center, is massive inside!//It must have taken a long time to build.

Text.SourceString: Vitamin D is good for you. You can get it by being outside.//It comes from the sun.
Text.LocalizedString: Vitamin D is good for you. You can get it by being outside.//It comes from the sun.

Text.SourceString: The animal shelter has so many black cats.//<portrait=happy>I like black cats! They’re so cool!
Text.LocalizedString: The animal shelter has so many black cats.//<portrait=happy>I like black cats! They’re so cool!

Text.SourceString: I want one!//Maybe two… I want all the animals.
Text.LocalizedString: I want one!//Maybe two… I want all the animals.
